paris-105-resources.def: This indicator shows the share of foreign support to statistics dedicated to demographic and social statistics received in past ten years.

paris-106-resources.def: This indicator shows the share of foreign support to statistics dedicated to economic statistics received in past ten years.

paris-107-resources.def: This indicator shows the share of foreign support to statistics dedicated to environmental and multi-sectoral statistics received in past ten years.

paris-108-resources.def: This indicator shows the share of foreign support to statistics dedicated to general data collection, preservation and dissemination received in past ten years.

paris-109-resources.def: This indicator captures whether the country is a small island developing state, as defined by UNSD.
paris-109-resources.source: United Nations Office of the High Representative for the Least Developed Countries, Landlocked Developing Countries and Small Island Developing States
paris-109-resources.dataset: United Nations Office of the High Representative for the Least Developed Countries, Landlocked Developing Countries and Small Island Developing States

paris-113-resources.def: The Statistical Capacity Indicator provides an overview of the capacity of a country's national statistical system based on a diagnostic framework thereby assessing three dimensions: Methodology, Source Data, and Periodicity and Timeliness.

paris-115-resources.def: This indicator measures the level of statistical literacy in the country. This score measures the first level of statistical literacy: consistent, non-critical use of statistics.

paris-116-resources.def: This indicator measures the level of statistical literacy in the country. This score measures the first level of statistical literacy: critical use of statistics.

paris-117-resources.def: This indicator measures the level of statistical literacy in the country. This score measures the first level of statistical literacy: critical mathematical use of statistics.

paris-121-resources.def: This indicator shows the total support to development in statistics received in the year of reference (in current USD).

paris-123-resources.def: This indicator shows the total support to development in statistics received in past three years (in current USD).

paris-136-resources.def: This indicator measures whether there is a national statistical plan under implementation (SDG 17.18.3)

paris-138-resources.def: This indicator measures whether the national statistical plan under implementation is fully funded.

paris-150-resources.def: Partitioning of the countries into four income groups according to WB Country and Lending Groups: High, Upper Middle, Lower Middle and Low Income using GNI per capita data.

paris-154-resources.def: World Bank Governance Indicator on Rule of Law. Rule of Law captures perceptions of the extent to which agents have confidence in and abide by the rules of society, and in particular the quality of contract enforcement, property rights, the police, and the courts, as well as the likelihood of crime and violence.
paris-154-resources.source: WGI are produced by Daniel Kaufmann (Natural Resource Governance Institute and Brookings Institution) and Aart Kraay (World Bank Development Research Group).
paris-154-resources.dataset: WGI are produced by Daniel Kaufmann (Natural Resource Governance Institute and Brookings Institution) and Aart Kraay (World Bank Development Research Group).

paris-165-resources.def: This indicator assesses the current status of the National Strategy for Development of Statistics (NSDS) in the country.

paris-167-resources.def: This indicator shows the share of foreign support to statistics dedicated to strategic and managerial issues of official statistics at national and international level received in past ten years.

paris-31-resources.def: This indicator measures whether a country is on the World Bank's Harmonized List of Fragile Situations.
paris-31-resources.source: World Bank Group’s (WBG) Fragile, Conflict and Violence Group
paris-31-resources.dataset: World Bank Group’s (WBG) Fragile, Conflict and Violence Group

paris-35-resources.def: GDP per capita is gross domestic product divided by midyear population.
paris-35-resources.source: World Bank national accounts data, and OECD National Accounts data files.
paris-35-resources.dataset: World Bank national accounts data, and OECD National Accounts data files.

paris-38-resources.def: Government finance accounting concept describes the accounting basis for reporting central government financial data.

paris-39-resources.def: This indicator assesses for African countries the capacity of statistical systems using a diagnostic framework which consists of three assessment areas: statistical methodology; source data; and periodicity and timeliness.

paris-42-resources.def: This indicator measures whether the country is eligible for borrowing from the International Development Association.
paris-42-resources.source: International Development Association World Bank Group
paris-42-resources.dataset: International Development Association World Bank Group

paris-45-resources.def: This indicator captures whether the country is a least developed country, defined by UNSD.
paris-45-resources.source: United Nations Office of the High Representative for the Least Developed Countries, Landlocked Developing Countries and Small Island Developing States
paris-45-resources.dataset: United Nations Office of the High Representative for the Least Developed Countries, Landlocked Developing Countries and Small Island Developing States

paris-49-resources.def: This indicator captures whether the country is a landlocked developing state, defined by UNSD.
paris-49-resources.source: United Nations Office of the High Representative for the Least Developed Countries, Landlocked Developing Countries and Small Island Developing States
paris-49-resources.dataset: United Nations Office of the High Representative for the Least Developed Countries, Landlocked Developing Countries and Small Island Developing States

paris-67-resources.def: This indicator measures whether there exists an agency/board/institution that advises the Chief Statistician on National Statistical Organization activities.

paris-92-resources.def: GDP per capita is the sum of gross value added by all resident producers in the economy plus any product taxes (less subsidies) not included in the valuation of output, divided by mid-year population.
paris-92-resources.source: World Bank national accounts data, and OECD National Accounts data files
paris-92-resources.dataset: World Bank national accounts data, and OECD National Accounts data files

paris-94-resources.def: Total number of people living in the country.
paris-94-resources.source: (1) United Nations Population Division. World Population Prospects: 2019 Revision. (2) Census reports and other statistical publications from national statistical offices, (3) Eurostat: Demographic Statistics, (4) United Nations Statistical Division. Population and Vital Statistics Reprot (various years), (5) U.S. Census Bureau: International Database, and (6) Secretariat of the Pacific Community: Statistics and Demography Programme.
paris-94-resources.dataset: (1) United Nations Population Division. World Population Prospects: 2019 Revision. (2) Census reports and other statistical publications from national statistical offices, (3) Eurostat: Demographic Statistics, (4) United Nations Statistical Division. Population and Vital Statistics Reprot (various years), (5) U.S. Census Bureau: International Database, and (6) Secretariat of the Pacific Community: Statistics and Demography Programme.

paris-99-resources.def: Primary completion rate (PCR) is the number of students successfully completing the last year of (or graduating from) primary school in a given year, divided by the number of children of official graduation age in the population.E100
paris-99-resources.source: UNESCO Institute for Statistics: Table 12: Measures of progression and completion in primary education (ISCED 1).
paris-99-resources.dataset: UNESCO Institute for Statistics: Table 12: Measures of progression and completion in primary education (ISCED 1).
